<i>Talk to Inspector Callahan.</i>
<i>He'll tell you I'm not a suspect.</i>

735
01:01:22,920 --> 01:01:25,047
<i>I have nothing</i>
<i>to do with these deaths.</i>

736
01:01:25,256 --> 01:01:27,622
<i>That's all I have to say, now sod off.</i>

737
01:01:28,025 --> 01:01:29,686
Callahan!

738
01:02:06,297 --> 01:02:07,764
You.

739
01:02:42,333 --> 01:02:43,459
Harry.

740
01:02:46,237 --> 01:02:48,432
I think that's about it for me.

741
01:02:52,343 --> 01:02:53,605
What's that tattoo?

742
01:02:54,278 --> 01:02:55,905
Oh, that.

743
01:02:56,113 --> 01:02:58,411
One of my grandfather's superstitions.

744
01:02:58,616 --> 01:03:02,279
You see, he painted these words
on my back and chest.

745
01:03:02,486 --> 01:03:06,115
It's supposed to ward off
anything that's harmful or evil.

746
01:03:06,324 --> 01:03:10,658
When he heard I was your partner,
he figured I could use the help.

747
01:03:10,861 --> 01:03:13,091
I was just trying
to honor the old guy.

748
01:03:13,831 --> 01:03:16,629
Besides, I didn't think it could hurt.

749
01:03:17,368 --> 01:03:19,836
Listen, I think I'm gonna go home.

750
01:03:20,037 --> 01:03:22,403
I'll catch you later for a beer.

751
01:03:59,176 --> 01:04:01,076
- See him?
- I saw him.

752
01:04:39,717 --> 01:04:41,275
He can't be over there.

753
01:04:41,852 --> 01:04:43,376
How y'all doing?

754
01:04:59,637 --> 01:05:01,730
You're the last asshole Janero sends.

755
01:05:01,939 --> 01:05:03,270
Wait, you got it wrong!

756
01:05:03,474 --> 01:05:06,807
Don't fuck with me, buddy.
I'll kick your ass right now.

757
01:05:07,011 --> 01:05:08,239
It's not what you think.

758
01:05:08,446 --> 01:05:10,414
Janero did hire us.

759
01:05:10,614 --> 01:05:12,479
But this ain't a hit.

760
01:05:12,683 --> 01:05:16,346
Janero doesn't want
anything to happen to you.

761
01:05:16,554 --> 01:05:17,486
We're your...

762
01:05:18,389 --> 01:05:19,481
...bodyguards.

763
01:05:30,301 --> 01:05:33,065
Those letters
all came from your files.

764
01:05:33,471 --> 01:05:35,996
Harlan Rook. God.

765
01:05:36,207 --> 01:05:37,572
Yes, I remember him.

766
01:05:37,775 --> 01:05:42,269
Every time I was at a film festival
or a seminar, he was there.

767
01:05:42,480 --> 01:05:46,712
Mr. IKKnow-It-AII, I called him.
He knew everything about my films.

768
01:05:48,219 --> 01:05:51,655
To tell the truth,
I found it a little unnerving.

769
01:05:52,523 --> 01:05:54,013
What'd he want?

770
01:05:54,825 --> 01:05:56,122
He had this screenplay...

771
01:05:56,327 --> 01:05:58,522
...for a horror film
he wanted me to direct.

772
01:05:58,729 --> 01:06:01,425
He said it'd be
the ultimate Peter Swan film.

773
01:06:01,632 --> 01:06:03,600
He was crazy.
I couldn't get rid of him.

774
01:06:03,801 --> 01:06:07,293
Finally, my attorney
put a restraining order on him.

775
01:06:07,505 --> 01:06:08,699
Then what happened?

776
01:06:08,906 --> 01:06:10,999
I didn't see or hear from him again.

777
01:06:11,208 --> 01:06:14,075
That must have been over a year ago.

778
01:06:15,513 --> 01:06:16,480
Is he the one?

779
01:06:16,680 --> 01:06:18,910
The typewriter
used on these letters...

780
01:06:19,116 --> 01:06:22,643
...is the same one used
to tip us off to the Dead Pool.

781
01:06:27,258 --> 01:06:30,557
Call Swan's attorney
and see what he knows about Rook.

782
01:06:30,761 --> 01:06:32,558
And run a DMV check.

783
01:06:32,763 --> 01:06:33,889
Right.

784
01:07:01,692 --> 01:07:05,958
It might not be a bad idea to start
playing it a little safe.

785
01:07:06,163 --> 01:07:08,358
Maybe your granddaddy can paint me up.

786
01:07:08,566 --> 01:07:10,431
Look, I'm being serious.

787
01:07:10,634 --> 01:07:14,570
Don't go where you normally go,
not even home. You can stay with me.

788
01:07:15,039 --> 01:07:18,202
Thanks, but I think I can
do a little better.

789
01:07:29,086 --> 01:07:30,610
Price of fame.

790
01:08:00,851 --> 01:08:04,378
Is this what Ackerman meant
by cooperating with the press?

791
01:08:04,588 --> 01:08:07,989
It must have been one of those
in-depth interviews.

792
01:08:18,903 --> 01:08:22,066
I got a lead on Rook.
A psychiatrist who treated him.

793
01:08:22,273 --> 01:08:23,501
Good.

794
01:08:26,577 --> 01:08:27,669
- Give it a try.
- Okay.

795
01:08:33,050 --> 01:08:36,110
It won't respond.
Someone's on my frequency.

796
01:08:49,266 --> 01:08:51,826
Forget it. It's just not working.

797
01:09:22,333 --> 01:09:24,198
Now what the hell is that?

798
01:12:43,167 --> 01:12:45,226
Time's up, Callahan.

799
01:13:22,673 --> 01:13:24,231
You all right, Al?

800
01:13:24,608 --> 01:13:26,132
Shit.

801
01:13:39,189 --> 01:13:40,781
Two fractured ribs.

802
01:13:41,325 --> 01:13:44,317
He bled in the chest.
We drained it and set up an IV.

803
01:13:44,528 --> 01:13:48,294
He's lucky, the bulletproof vest
he had on saved his life.

804
01:13:49,166 --> 01:13:51,760
Another of my
grandfather's superstitions.

805
01:13:51,969 --> 01:13:54,028
When your partner gives you advice...

806
01:13:54,238 --> 01:13:55,205
...take it.

807
01:13:56,440 --> 01:13:57,907
Harry.

808
01:14:06,483 --> 01:14:10,317
This is Dr. Friedman, chief
psychiatrist here at the hospital.

809
01:14:10,520 --> 01:14:12,181
I'm sorry about what happened.

810
01:14:12,389 --> 01:14:14,186
I feel somewhat responsible.

811
01:14:14,391 --> 01:14:17,519
Your partner contacted me about
a former patient of ours.

812
01:14:17,728 --> 01:14:19,252
- Harlan Rook?
- Yes.

813
01:14:19,463 --> 01:14:23,126
At first, I didn't recall the name.
I found the file today.

814
01:14:23,900 --> 01:14:25,993
He was evaluated here a year ago.

815
01:14:26,203 --> 01:14:28,671
The diagnosis was
process schizophrenia.

816
01:14:28,872 --> 01:14:30,305
Multiple personality.

817
01:14:30,507 --> 01:14:31,337
Exactly.

818
01:14:32,009 --> 01:14:33,977
His sense of self-hate
was so strong...

819
01:14:34,177 --> 01:14:37,271
...that he no longer had
any personality of his own.

820
01:14:37,481 --> 01:14:40,939
Consequently,
he substituted identities...

821
01:14:41,151 --> 01:14:43,619
...found in books, films...

822
01:14:43,820 --> 01:14:45,253
...fan magazines.

823
01:14:45,455 --> 01:14:48,481
Identities with which he had
love-hate relationships.

824
01:14:48,692 --> 01:14:51,058
He wasn't dangerous enough to hold?

825
01:14:51,261 --> 01:14:54,662
Most mentally ill people
are not violent, inspector.

826
01:14:54,865 --> 01:14:59,529
By law, a person who poses no danger
can only be held for 72 hours.

827
01:15:00,570 --> 01:15:04,370
I'm sorry, this is one instance
where the system failed.

828
01:15:04,574 --> 01:15:06,337
Is this address recent?

829
01:15:06,543 --> 01:15:07,976
I assume it's still the same.

830
01:15:12,082 --> 01:15:13,276
Samantha Walker.

831
01:15:13,483 --> 01:15:15,542
<i>This is Peter Swan, Ms. Walker.</i>

832
01:15:15,752 --> 01:15:18,585
<i>Your coverage of my predicament</i>
<i>has been thorough...</i>

833
01:15:18,789 --> 01:15:22,281
<i>... but my side hasn't been told</i>
<i>as well as it could be.</i>

834
01:15:22,492 --> 01:15:23,754
I see.

835
01:15:23,960 --> 01:15:27,088
<i>I'm prepared to grant you</i>
<i>an exclusive interview.</i>

836
01:15:27,297 --> 01:15:29,197
<i>Are you interested?</i>

837
01:15:34,104 --> 01:15:35,571
No doubt about it.

838
01:15:35,772 --> 01:15:37,103
He's our boy, Harry.

839
01:15:37,307 --> 01:15:40,435
Explosives. Caps.

840
01:15:40,644 --> 01:15:41,770
Detonator.

841
01:15:41,978 --> 01:15:43,036
It all connects.

842
01:15:43,613 --> 01:15:45,581
Harry, you gotta see this.

843
01:15:50,454 --> 01:15:52,115
Talk about obsession.

844
01:16:08,805 --> 01:16:12,502
Looks like he had a real
Peter Swan shrine going here.

845
01:16:15,278 --> 01:16:17,143
I'm not sure.

846
01:16:17,347 --> 01:16:19,747
I could have sworn I put it in my bag.

847
01:16:19,950 --> 01:16:22,009
But I'm not sure.

848
01:16:22,219 --> 01:16:25,746
- Bob, do you have my little mike?
- It's in your bag.

849
01:16:25,956 --> 01:16:27,355
Thank you.

850
01:17:05,929 --> 01:17:07,089
Look at this.

851
01:17:10,133 --> 01:17:12,294
I'll call the TV station.

852
01:17:24,514 --> 01:17:28,416
Samantha went out to the shipyard
to interview Peter Swan.

853
01:17:28,618 --> 01:17:30,711
Swan doesn't know anything about it.

854
01:17:30,921 --> 01:17:33,151
- What's this?
- A payroll stub.

855
01:17:33,356 --> 01:17:36,655
Sundown Security, made out to
Ed Butler? I don't get it.

856
01:17:36,860 --> 01:17:40,591
That's the company that provides
security for Swan's locations.

857
01:17:40,797 --> 01:17:43,493
Ed Butler may be an alias for Rook.

858
01:17:43,700 --> 01:17:45,827
Where are you going? Harry?

859
01:17:46,036 --> 01:17:47,765
Harry!

860
01:17:47,971 --> 01:17:49,836
That's my car!

861
01:17:57,814 --> 01:17:58,644
Yes.

862
01:17:58,849 --> 01:18:00,749
That's the shot I'm looking for.

863
01:18:12,262 --> 01:18:14,059
What is it you want from me?

864
01:18:14,264 --> 01:18:16,630
You've got it wrong, love.

865
01:18:17,267 --> 01:18:19,292
This is what you wanted.

866
01:18:19,603 --> 01:18:22,367
An exclusive interview.

867
01:18:23,273 --> 01:18:24,535
But you're not Swan.

868
01:18:24,741 --> 01:18:26,766
Shut up! You don't know!

869
01:18:26,977 --> 01:18:29,104
You don't know!

870
01:18:29,946 --> 01:18:31,641
I know who I am.

871
01:18:32,315 --> 01:18:33,748
Do you know who you are?

872
01:18:34,150 --> 01:18:34,980
Do you?!

873
01:18:35,185 --> 01:18:36,550
Yes.

874
01:18:36,920 --> 01:18:38,387
All those films he made.

875
01:18:38,588 --> 01:18:40,783
Those are my nightmares, not his!

876
01:18:41,558 --> 01:18:45,619
Every night I dream,
and somehow he reads my mind.

877
01:18:45,829 --> 01:18:47,990
He stole my thoughts.

878
01:18:48,198 --> 01:18:52,794
He put my thoughts on film,
and he takes all the credit.

879
01:18:54,905 --> 01:18:56,930
He can't get away with it.

880
01:18:59,576 --> 01:19:01,373
He has to pay.

881
01:19:07,517 --> 01:19:09,644
He stole my nightmares
and made them real.

882
01:19:09,853 --> 01:19:11,718
So I stole his Dead Pool.

883
01:19:12,222 --> 01:19:14,816
I'll play his game and make it real.

884
01:19:17,360 --> 01:19:19,055
He can take credit for that.

885
01:20:44,948 --> 01:20:45,880
Drop it, Rook.

886
01:20:46,082 --> 01:20:50,314
You didn't die, Callahan,
so I had to find another celebrity.

887
01:20:54,824 --> 01:20:55,722
You're next.

888
01:20:55,925 --> 01:20:58,359
Shoot me, Callahan.

889
01:20:58,561 --> 01:21:00,119
Maybe you'll get lucky.

890
01:21:00,330 --> 01:21:04,289
Maybe my muscles won't contract
and drive this knife into her throat.

891
01:21:05,869 --> 01:21:06,893
Let her go.

892
01:21:07,737 --> 01:21:09,034
First the gun.

893
01:21:09,239 --> 01:21:11,366
Drop it and kick it over to me.

894
01:21:15,478 --> 01:21:17,207
Time's up. What's it gonna be?

895
01:21:25,822 --> 01:21:27,084
What the fuck?

896
01:21:31,961 --> 01:21:34,293
You've locked yourself in, asshole.

897
01:21:34,831 --> 01:21:36,230
Yeah.

898
01:21:36,433 --> 01:21:38,230
Just you and me, asshole.

899
01:21:40,970 --> 01:21:42,403
The gun, Callahan.

900
01:21:44,274 --> 01:21:45,104
Now!

901
01:21:45,308 --> 01:21:46,172
No!

902
01:21:46,376 --> 01:21:48,071
He'll kill us both!

903
01:21:50,780 --> 01:21:52,145
Oh, God.

904
01:22:02,358 --> 01:22:06,124
You let me down,
Mr. Famous-Fucking-Cop.

905
01:22:06,496 --> 01:22:08,157
You let Swan get away.

906
01:22:08,364 --> 01:22:09,956
You're the killer, not Swan.

907
01:22:10,266 --> 01:22:11,995
I should have killed you first.

908
01:22:12,202 --> 01:22:14,170
That was my big mistake.

909
01:22:14,471 --> 01:22:15,768
Now kick it over to me.

910
01:22:17,640 --> 01:22:19,608
Harry, don't.

911
01:22:28,518 --> 01:22:30,076
Think you're smart, don't you?

912
01:22:47,270 --> 01:22:49,135
Callahan, you son of a bitch!

913
01:22:55,111 --> 01:22:56,942
I'm gonna kill you slow!

914
01:23:02,085 --> 01:23:04,076
Do you hear that, Callahan?!

915
01:24:20,930 --> 01:24:22,659
Stay in there.

916
01:25:31,868 --> 01:25:33,733
Callahan!

917
01:25:41,344 --> 01:25:43,539
Come on out, Callahan.

918
01:25:56,359 --> 01:25:58,725
There's nowhere left to run, Callahan.

919
01:25:59,662 --> 01:26:01,687
Don't make me come in and get you.

920
01:26:05,535 --> 01:26:07,162
The game's over!

921
01:26:07,370 --> 01:26:08,735
You're out of bullets.

922
01:26:38,568 --> 01:26:40,160
You know what that means.

923
01:26:42,271 --> 01:26:43,670
You're shit out of luck.

924
01:27:28,851 --> 01:27:31,752
- Where's Rook?
- He's hanging out back there.

925
01:27:37,226 --> 01:27:40,127
Inspector, was this another
hit attempt by Janero?

926
01:27:40,329 --> 01:27:42,889
Is it connected to the Dead Pool case?

